    "Management": {
      "text": "Nonoperative management is successful in >90% of patients who are hemodynamically stable\nLow-grade injuries (grades I–III) can almost always be managed without surgery\nHigher-grade injuries commonly fail nonoperative therapy.\nConsider angiographic embolization if:\nLarge amount of hemoperitoneum\nVascular injury (contrast blush) on CT",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
